      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRALEE DIGBY (7) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at Taree Super Track over 300m behind Done By Noon (18.85) in a Grade 5. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Looks the one to beat on his best form. FRAME SISTER (5) finds it hard to break through. Continues to race well, filling the minors at the last four starts, the latest when second (25.71) at this track. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Well-placed to take this out. WOOPI EXPRESS (1) drifted back settling but did best work late to finish 5th at Richmond over 320m (19.02). Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Can figure in the finish. TAP OUT POPPY (6) has strong claims after a close top-three finish last time out.",
